article.headline: Fordham 24, Holy Cross 21
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- James Crockett recovered a fumble in the end zone and came up with a big interception to help Fordham beat Holy Cross 24-21 Saturday. Dominic Randolph tossed a 2-yard TD pass to Randolph McDermott with 4:06 left to pull Holy Cross within three. The Crusaders (6-3, 3-1 Patriot League) got the ball back but Crockett picked off Randolph at the Fordham 20 with 10 seconds to go. Jonte Coven had 29 carries for 167 yards and John Skelton tossed a 26-yard TD pass for the Rams (8-2, 5-0). Coven's 61-yard run in the first quarter gave Fordham a 7-0 lead. Randolph completed 32 of 53 passes for 309 yards and three touchdowns with one interception. McDermott finished with nine receptions for 106 yards and two scores. Crockett's fumble recovery made it 21-7 in the third.
